After she approached me, 2 other nice ladies approached me and asked if I was already being helped. I replied yes and this was the turning point where everything started getting good. About as close as S Florida gets to a redneck bar between Davie and Homestead with its own unique Miami twist. And, unlike most of Miami, it doesn’t pretend to be anything it’s not. Edible pub food, good drinks, reasonably priced, and pool tables in the back. But the real treat is the cast of characters, regulars and tourists, that wander in. Sit down, relax and strike up a conversation. Tucked away on the 9th floor of a residential building up a creaky, cranky, elevator, Mike’s is a great place, long may it live!

Downtown Miami's best kept secret: on the 9th floor of a condo there's this wonderful, absolutely amazing, family-owned Irish sports pub. Its food is the best happy hour grub you'll get this side of Wynwood, $2 pints on Tuesdays, and legendary specials on game night and St. Patrick's. The friendly staff treats clients as family, and whether you're at the outside tables, indoor booths, the bar, or the pool room, you'll get exceptional service.  On top of that, they've got cheap valet parking and are within walking distance of the Omni metromover and bus station.  It's an absolutely wonderful place: if you're in the downtown area and want a great place for food, drinks, to meet with clients or to wind down, I can't recommend this place any higher.

Me and my boyfriend were trying to find a late night eatery and came across this place based off reviews. Right off the bat when I was calling to ask what time they closed some guy on the phone answered me rudely and had an attitude over the phone and hung up immediately after abruptly after he answered my question. I brushed it off as nothing and thought they must be really busy. When we got there ,the waitress on the floor was kind to let us know they were closed but the bar was open with a late night menu. For 10 minutes at the bar me and my boyfriend were waiting for someone to help us and tried to get a female bartender attention but she looked back and kept walking off. Again I brushed off the fact that she was busy. The late night menu was a huge disappointment it was more like a diner menu than a pub menu where I could easily get any of these items for cheaper at a fast food restaurant. But we stayed because we were hungry and we didn't know where else to go. When we were ready to order I asked a question first about something on the menu and wasn't finished to have the male bartender walk away to talk to someone else. Yet again tried to get someone attention to take our order. Both bartenders seemed to be more occupied to make sure everyone else was taken care of with a smile. The food was nothing special and mediocre. $9 for 3 chicken strips and had to pay for fries separately.I was ready to leave so I asked for a to go box for our food, it took the guy 5 minutes to get it because he was so busy talking away with everyone else and kind you there was only like less than 20 people in that bar who already had ordered something and has it in front of them. I will never waste my money there again. Unfriendly customer service and overpriced "late night menu ."
